Such an extravagant undeveloping move is possible here, due to the closed
nature of the centre. The point is that Black wants to develop the g8-knight
via e7 and also not have to worry about the sensitive g7-pawn which often gets
attacked in this variation.} (5... Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Ba6 7. Bxa6 Nxa6 8. Qg4 $1 {
