12. Rac1 {The position has arisen from a Queen's Gambit Declined and Black has
employed a Stonewall pawn set-up (f5-e6-d5-c6) to control the centre. White is
better here, due to the passive nature of the bishop on c8 and the fact that
the black pawns limit its scope. Moreover, here Black loses patience and
embarks on a faulty plan:} g5 $2 {EXERCISE: Black dreams of pushing the knight
on f3 away, before swinging the rook and the queen to the h-file. How should
White react to this?} (12... Nf6 {followed by connecting the rooks is a much
better plan.}) 13. Nd2 $1 {ANSWER: A great move! White's plan, which is
typical when the opponent carries out a flank attack, is to counter in the
centre of the board. By retreating the knight, White will play f2-f3 and e3-e4,
opening lines towards the black king. He also removes the knight from a square
where it would have been a target for the ...g5-g4 push.} Rf7 (13... g4 {would
have been met by} 14. f3 $1 Nf6 15. Rce1 Bd7 16. fxg4 fxg4 {when} 17. e4 $1 {
would leave White with a clear advantage.}) 14. f3 e5 $5 {EXERCISE: Black
continues to play boldly, but due to the better development of his pieces,
with accurate play White can gain a clear advantage. Can you see how to do
this? --- ANSWER:} 15. cxd5 cxd5 16. e4 $1 {After this move Black's position
falls apart with alarming speed.} fxe4 ({Keeping lines closed with something
like} 16... Nb6 17. dxe5 Be6 {is necessary, although Black remains in big
trouble as he has a pawn less.}) 17. fxe4 Rxf1+ 18. Rxf1 exd4 {EXERCISE: If
White makes the obvious recapture, Black can get the queens off with 19...Qc5.
Can you find a stronger way to play? --- ANSWER:} 19. Qc7 $1 {Absolutely
crushing! This ties down the knight on d7 and the black queen is shackled to
defending the back rank. The rest is easy.} Kg7 20. Rf5 dxe4 21. Nxe4 Qb4 22.
Rxg5+ {. The g5-pawn, which was designed to be used as an attacking weapon,
falls and the black king is doomed.} (22. -- {Summary: The main reason that
Black's strategy didn't work in this game was down to the fact that the centre
wasn't closed and White was able to open it rapidly. As a side issue, Black's
development was also lagging which meant that once files became open he was
unable to defend his king in an adequate manner. Be very careful before
employing a strategy such as the kingside pawnstorm!}) 1-0

