1. -- {Closed Centres make Flank Attacks more effective: With a closed centre
the kingside pawn-storm becomes a much more reasonable strategy, which is
logical as play is directed towards the flanks in such situations. This is
most markedly shown in the King's Indian Defence, where often White employs a
queenside attack and Black a kingside attack. The following is a modern
classic in this particular opening and one of the games that made me take up
the opening!} *

