{, attacking the f2-square.}) 25... Rd2 26. Qf3 Qa7 27. Nd7 Nd8 $6 {Perhaps
understandably Shirov decides to give back the exchange in order to try and
activate his knight, but his position remains pretty rotten.} (27... Ra8 28.
Ne7+ (28. Bc4 $5 {to activate the bishop is maybe what White had in mind})
28... Kh8 29. Qxf7 Rxd3 30. Nf8 $1 Qa2 {is probably a draw after} 31. Neg6+
hxg6 32. Nxg6+ Kh7 33. Nf8+ Kh8 ({but not} 33... Rxf8 34. Qxa2 {.})) 28. Nxf8
