cleanest way to finish Black off? --- ANSWER:} 36. Ra1 $1 {The rook enters the
game with decisive effect.} Qd4 (36... Qxc4 37. Ra7+ Kf6 38. Qxd8+ Kg6 39.
Qxd6+ {is also over, as long as White doesn't fall into a perpetual check on
the c1- and f4-squares.}) 37. Ra3 Bc1 38. Ne3 {. Black is forced to take the
knight and is just an exchange and a pawn down.} (38. -- {Summary: White
focused his attention on playing against the knight on b7 and the bishop on h6.
