1. -- {Seizing and Developing the Initiative: Of all the great champions,
Garry Kasparov is perhaps the most famous for his ability to seize the
initiative out of the opening, often playing with ferocious energy and
crushing his opponents, even with Black. This was thanks largely to his
dynamic opening repertoire which he worked very hard on. Here is an early game
played by the fourteen year-old Kasparov.} *

