1. -- {Neutralizing the Initiative: The difficulty level of successfully
neutralizing an initiative depends, of course, on how serious it is in the
first place. We have seen some examples so far of how an initiative can
snowball into a dangerous and potentially winning position quite quickly. It
is important to sense the danger early and deal with threats precisely, so
that they don't grow into something more serious. One of the best players in
the world at doing this is the current World Champion Vishy Anand.} *

