1. -- {The Long-Term Initiative: Despite the fact that most of the time the
initiative is short lived, certain openings give rise to longer-term
advantages, thanks to the presence of static factors, such as superior piece
activity or a better pawn structure. A good example of this is the Benko or
Volga Gambit. The Volga Gambit was its original name (after the longest river
in Europe that runs through Russia), but due to the work of the Hungarian
Grandmaster Pal Benko with the opening, his name stuck in English-speaking
countries. I hope that the next game demonstrates what I mean about the
longer-term initiative.} *

