{King Safety: After the initial material evaluation is done, we must turn our
eyes towards the positional features which are prominent and it will often be
the case that something will strike you immediately. King Safety often
overrides the material situation. In fact if the king is in immediate peril
then that is normally going to be the factor that decides the game. The
following is a basic example of this.} 1. -- {White is a rook and two minor
pieces down but that doesn't matter - the material is irrelevant as he is
about to win by checkmate! --- Some may even start by trying to evaluate the
king safety before the material balance and I don't think there is a right or
wrong way round to do this. Personally I evaluate the material first because
it's more clear cut - one side will be up or down, whereas king safety can be
a little more difficult to assess.} *

