his queen.} ({Actually} 25. gxf3 {also wins:} exf3 26. Kh1 Qh3 27. Rg1 {and
Black is out of ideas.}) 25... Qd7 (25... Qxe5 26. dxe5 Bg4 27. a4 {is an
opposite-coloured bishop ending that White will win due to the a- and b-pawns.}
) 26. a4 {. There is of course some play left in the position, but White is
